obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line 3
  line `THE INDI A N ANTARCTIC ACT, 2022`
  line ______________
  line `ARRANGEMENT OF SECTIONS`
  line ______________
  line `CHAPTER I`
  line `P RELIMINARY`
  line `S ECTIONS.`
  line `1. Short title and commencement.`
  line `2. Application.`
  line `3. Definitions.`
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line `R EQUIREMENT AS TO PERMIT`
  line `4. Permit for Indian expedition to Antarctica.`
  line `5. Permit for Indian station in Antarctica.`
  line `6. Permit for vessel and aircraft entering Antarctica.`
  line `7. Permit for mineral resource activities.`
  line `8. Permit for certain activities in Antarctica.`
  line `9. Permit for introducing non - native animals and plants into Antarctica.`
  line `10. Permit for introducing microscopic organisms.`
  line `11. Permit to enter protected areas.`
  line `12. Permit for waste disposal.`
  line `13. Permit for discharge into sea.`
  line `14. Permit for removal of biological specimen or any other sample from Antarctica.`
  line `15. Certain provisions not to apply during emergencies.`
  line `16. Special permit for commercial fishing in Antarctica.`
  line `CHAPTER III`
  line `P ROHIBITIONS`
  line `17. Prohibition of nuclear explosion or disposal of radioactive waste material in Antarctica.`
  line `18. Prohibition of introducing non - sterile soil in Antarctica.`
  line `19. Prohibition of introducing specified substances and products.`
  line `20. Prohibition relating to historic sites and monuments.`
  line `21. Prohibition of possessing, selling, etc.`
  line `22. Prohibition of discharge of certain products or substances.`
  line `CHAPTER IV`
  line `C OMMITTEE ON A NTARCTIC G OVERNANCE AND E NVIRONMENTAL P ROTECTION`
  line `23. Constitution of Committee.`
  line `24. Meetings of Committee.`
  line `25. Functions of Committee.`
  line `26. Power of Central Government to give directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
